President Jacob Zuma has declared a Special Provincial official funeral for Ramaphosa s spokesperson, Ronnie Mamoepa who passed way on on Saturday.The President has ordered that the National Flag be flown at half-mast at every flag station in the Gauteng province on Saturday, 29 July on the day of the funeral.Mamoepa passed away on Saturday in a Pretoria hospital at the age of on 56. We have lost one of the most outstanding communicators of the work of government and a renowned mediator of information between government and the communities we serve, through the media. I wish to once again convey our heartfelt condolences to the Mamoepa family, friends and relatives as well as comrades in his political home, the African National Congress. We share their loss deeply. May his soul rest in peace, said Zuma.Mamoepa has worked as Spokesperson for the first Gauteng Premier Tokyo Sexwale between 1994 and 1996. He also served as a Chief Director of Communication and Spokesperson to former President Thabo Mbeki.His latest role was serving as Spokesperson for the Deputy President which he started in 2014. He will fondly and forever be remembered for his humour and humility as well as the sterling work he displayed during his extensive spell in government where he served various government departments and political principals as spokesperson with distinction until his untimely death, the presidency said in a statement.Further details regarding his memorial service and the funeral will be communicated by the Gauteng Provincial Government.-TNA Reporter 